Source: SANZ Glossary Building Terminology
Author:
Vol / Page: 129
Edition:
Quote: <i>Water right- </i>A right granted under the provisions of the New Zealand Water and Soil Conservation Act 1967 and subsequent amendments by Regional Water Board (or the National Water and Soil Conservation Authority for applications by the Crown) authorizing the taking, using, damming or diverting of natural water, or the discharge of waste into natural water or on to the ground where natural water may be affected.
